data.name: labelHelpMechanicsLog.ToolTip
data.value: Mechanics Log is an unofficial addon developed by a 3rd party developer. With this addon you can see which person failed mechanics during a fight. It also shows you at what time a person failed what mechanic.

data.name: richTextBoxAbout.Text
data.value: Raid Tool made by Bram L. • ArcUpdater On this tab you can Install/Update/Delete certain components. • Logs On this tab you can list all the logs and upload logs for an entire week to GW2Raidar. • About Information about the tool. • Useful Links Some links that might are useful to access. • Settings Customize your settings for the tool here, remember to hit the 'Save Settings' button to save them.

data.name: labelHelpLogFilter.ToolTip
data.value: Selected week: Filter for the week you want to upload. Only selected week: Only Upload the selected week. (Recommended) Raid: Show/Upload Raid logs Fractal: Show/Upload Raid logs Mini-Raid: Show/Upload Mini Raid logs (Berg, Zane, Narella etc.) Kitty: Kitty Golems (Dps Golems) Local Logs: Show the logs in your log folder Raidar Logs: Show the encounters connected to your GW2Raidar account Update List: Update the list based on your selected filters. Tag: Give the logs you want to upload a tag. Upload Logs: Upload the logs shown on screen.

data.name: label5.ToolTip
data.value:
GW2 Install Folder is used to install/update/delete ArcDps components. ArcDps Log Folder is used to list all the logs and needed to upload them.
GW2Raidar section • Username and Password Required to login to GW2Raidar's API if you want to upload logs. • Remember password saved your password in the config file. Config file location: %appdata%\Roaming\GW2BLinssenRaidTool • Display password shows your password in plain text. • Test Login, click this to try to login to API with your account details.
File Types • Evtc (uncompressed) • Zip (compressed) Choose the file types which your ArcDps makes. (Both possible)
Make sure to hit Save Settings to save your settings to the config file.
